<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1227,1903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1227,1254]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished among 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1891" box="[532,698,1228,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Schizopteridae</taxonomicName>
by the truncate three-segmented labium (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1269,1228,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scanning electron micrographs of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Head and thorax, ventral view. B. Head, frontal view. C. Detail of mso. D. Abdomen, ventral view. E. Detail of sterna 4, 5, and 6. F. Pygophore, ventral view.Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, lb1 = first labial segment, lb2 = second labial segment, lb3 = third labial segment, mso = male-specific organ, oc = ocellus, phs4 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 4, phs5 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 5, pyc = pygophore cavity, pyg = pygophore. Scale bars: 200 µm (Fig. 2A); 100 µm (Fig. 2B;2D); 20 µm (Fig. 2C); 50 µm (Fig. 2E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); the forewing with two marginal cells heavily sclerotized and rest of forewing membranous (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1110,1264,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1588,1613]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral left view. D. Frontal view. Abbreviation: mso = male-specific organ. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); absence of a pronotal collar (
<figureCitation box="[160,295,1300,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1588,1613]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral left view. D. Frontal view. Abbreviation: mso = male-specific organ. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1A; 1D</figureCitation>
); presence of distinct hyperpleural lobes; male frons with a male-specific organ (mso, 
<figureCitation box="[1252,1343,1300,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1588,1613]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral left view. D. Frontal view. Abbreviation: mso = male-specific organ. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Figs 1D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1355,1369,1300,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scanning electron micrographs of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Head and thorax, ventral view. B. Head, frontal view. C. Detail of mso. D. Abdomen, ventral view. E. Detail of sterna 4, 5, and 6. F. Pygophore, ventral view.Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, lb1 = first labial segment, lb2 = second labial segment, lb3 = third labial segment, mso = male-specific organ, oc = ocellus, phs4 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 4, phs5 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 5, pyc = pygophore cavity, pyg = pygophore. Scale bars: 200 µm (Fig. 2A); 100 µm (Fig. 2B;2D); 20 µm (Fig. 2C); 50 µm (Fig. 2E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
B–C), covered by dense pale setae; sterna 4 and 5 each with patches of hairlike sensillae (phs4 and phs5, 
<figureCitation box="[1247,1312,1336,1362]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scanning electron micrographs of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Head and thorax, ventral view. B. Head, frontal view. C. Detail of mso. D. Abdomen, ventral view. E. Detail of sterna 4, 5, and 6. F. Pygophore, ventral view.Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, lb1 = first labial segment, lb2 = second labial segment, lb3 = third labial segment, mso = male-specific organ, oc = ocellus, phs4 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 4, phs5 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 5, pyc = pygophore cavity, pyg = pygophore. Scale bars: 200 µm (Fig. 2A); 100 µm (Fig. 2B;2D); 20 µm (Fig. 2C); 50 µm (Fig. 2E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D–E); ventral side of the pygophore (pyg) with a pygophore cavity (pyc, 
<figureCitation box="[856,989,1372,1398]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scanning electron micrographs of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Head and thorax, ventral view. B. Head, frontal view. C. Detail of mso. D. Abdomen, ventral view. E. Detail of sterna 4, 5, and 6. F. Pygophore, ventral view.Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, lb1 = first labial segment, lb2 = second labial segment, lb3 = third labial segment, mso = male-specific organ, oc = ocellus, phs4 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 4, phs5 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 5, pyc = pygophore cavity, pyg = pygophore. Scale bars: 200 µm (Fig. 2A); 100 µm (Fig. 2B;2D); 20 µm (Fig. 2C); 50 µm (Fig. 2E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2D; 2F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1227,1903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1407,1434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Small (
<quantity box="[505,674,1408,1435]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.16" pageId="1" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="1.23" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.16">1.16–1.30 mm</quantity>
), macropterous, body elongate ovoid (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1169,1408,1434]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1588,1613]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,409,1568]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral left view. D. Frontal view. Abbreviation: mso = male-specific organ. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–C). COLORATION. General coloration brown with yellow appendages, and white fascia on corium and clavus. SURFACE AND VES- TITURE. Body, except appendages and abdominal terga with dense microtrichia; head, pronotum and wing veins with short to medium-length light brown setae, abdomen densely covered with elongate, light brown setae; malespecific organ with long dense light setae overgrown. STRUCTURE. Ocelli (oc, 
<figureCitation box="[1046,1130,1552,1578]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scanning electron micrographs of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Head and thorax, ventral view. B. Head, frontal view. C. Detail of mso. D. Abdomen, ventral view. E. Detail of sterna 4, 5, and 6. F. Pygophore, ventral view.Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, lb1 = first labial segment, lb2 = second labial segment, lb3 = third labial segment, mso = male-specific organ, oc = ocellus, phs4 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 4, phs5 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 5, pyc = pygophore cavity, pyg = pygophore. Scale bars: 200 µm (Fig. 2A); 100 µm (Fig. 2B;2D); 20 µm (Fig. 2C); 50 µm (Fig. 2E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) about the same size as that of one ommatidium, close to anterior-ventral margin of eye; third labial segment blunt; pronotum trapezoidal; scutellum triangular, with rounded tip; tarsal formula 3-3-3; bladder-like arolia present on fore and mid legs; abdomen symmetrical, with six visible sterna corresponding to segments 2+3, 4, 5, 6, 7, and pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1308,1660,1686]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1367,166,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scanning electron micrographs of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Head and thorax, ventral view. B. Head, frontal view. C. Detail of mso. D. Abdomen, ventral view. E. Detail of sterna 4, 5, and 6. F. Pygophore, ventral view.Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, lb1 = first labial segment, lb2 = second labial segment, lb3 = third labial segment, mso = male-specific organ, oc = ocellus, phs4 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 4, phs5 = patch of hairlike sensillae on sternum 5, pyc = pygophore cavity, pyg = pygophore. Scale bars: 200 µm (Fig. 2A); 100 µm (Fig. 2B;2D); 20 µm (Fig. 2C); 50 µm (Fig. 2E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
); mediotergite 7 (mt7) rectangular, mediotergite 8 (mt8) roughly rectangular, narrow, with medial hook-shaped process (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1430,1455]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,174,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,1411]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Pygophore and genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, ano = anophore, at = anal tube, lp = left paramere, mt7 = mediotergite 7, mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = process of mediotergite 8, pyg = pygophore, rp = right paramere. Scale bar: 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628965/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). GENITALIA (
<figureCitation box="[372,462,1732,1758]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1430,1455]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,174,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,1411]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia of Voragocoris weirauchae sp.n. A. Pygophore and genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, ano = anophore, at = anal tube, lp = left paramere, mt7 = mediotergite 7, mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = process of mediotergite 8, pyg = pygophore, rp = right paramere. Scale bar: 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3628965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3628965/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Pygophore weakly asymmetrical; right paramere (rp) long, slightly curved, gradually tapering toward apex; left paramere (lp) smaller than right, roughly as long as wide; aedeagus (aed) devoid of visible conjunctival appendages, forming about one coil, tapering toward apex; anophore (ano) sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1227,1903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Female. Similar to male in overall habitus, macropterous, body elongate ovoid. Frons without dense setation. Abdominal sterna 4 and 5 without patches of hairlike sensillae. Genitalia vestigial.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
